prints the name, version and other details about the current machine and the operating system.
For basic usage, just execute the 'uname' command sans options.
--> uname

To print the kernel name
--> uname -s

To print the kernel release
--> uname -r

To print the kernel version
--> uname -v

To print the hostname
--> uname -n

To print machine hardware name 
--> uname - m

To print processor type 
--> uname -p

To print the operating system
--> uname -o

To print all information in one go
--> uname -a


